Product.Caption: Beautiful, comfortable, fabric and warm leather mixed with metal and wood are the hallmarks of our Alder and Tweed Collection. Check out our chairs, settees, benches, bar stools and tables. We're pretty sure you'll find just the piece you want to upgrade your home.

Solid pine, purposely given an aged and antique look, makes up the Rustic Antique Collection. Some are multi-colored, as is the way with antique furniture, some are just aged to perfection. You will so enjoy this collection that looks to have been left to you by your grandparents.

Rustic furniture produced with high quality select woods and handcrafted by true artisans makes up the Artisan furniture collection. Broken out into myriad collections, these wonderful pieces of furniture all have slightly different looks--using different woods, accents, styles, and finishes, but all will give you the same dependable quality and durability. Enjoy looking through what this collection offers . . . you are bound to find something you really love!

For our Rustic Autumn collection, solid alder wood is picked for its best grains, then the pieces are cut with a circle saw to give them the rough lines and look of truly rustic furniture. The pieces undergo a special antiquing process comprised of numerous finishing steps, and the resulting furniture shows the lovely grains and knots of the wood through its staining and finishing. Practical, durable, and beautiful, you will bequeath this furniture to your children and grandchildren.

Our Barnwood Renaissance collection uses all the skill and craftsmanship used to create our Montana Renaissance collection of furniture, but adds the further enhancement of combining a lovely recovered and reclaimed wood taken from old barns and structures, with the rich and beautifully grained, easily sustainable alder. The resulting look is one of aged quality and striking multicolored, multitextured depth. We think you will agree that this particular collection is perfect for unique rusticity.

We have gathered numerous collections of quality rustic bedroom furniture to appeal to a variety of individual tastes. Craftsmen from Montana, Colorado, Utah, and beyond have taken great pride in designing many of the rustic bedroom suites we offer on our site. Whether you want reclaimed wood that may have been beams from an original homestead or young saplings from a managed second growth forest we showcase it here. Purchase a simple loft or futon or indulge in an entire rustic bedroom suite for a larger area.

Shopping at rusticfurniture.com is a breeze when you are in the market for a rustic bed. We offer everything from the rustic trundle that fits under your bunk or regular frame to a massive tree branch four post king bed. Montana Lodge offers five collections featuring rustic beds of reclaimed woods, aspen, pine, and cedar. Frontier log beds include twins, bunks, loft beds, beds over futons, and queen or king, all with logs fashioned and hand peeled the old fashioned way. All log beds can be skip or clean peeled or have the rustic bark finish showing the warm cambium layer. Our alder beds, crafted in Montana feature light or heavy distress and two shades of a warm waxed hand rubbed finish. We also offer imported rustic beds crafted of beautiful hardwoods indigenous to India. To make your shopping easier all twin to queen beds shipping from Montana can have quality mattresses added into your package.

Rustic benches have come a long way and have a multitude of uses. Sit on a half log bench and take your shoes off in the mud room or place one of the custom benches beside your favorite trestle or farm dining table to add a couple of extra spots for the family dinner. Transport yourself back one hundred years and purchase one of the lovely historic Old Hickory benches constructed of second growth hickory saplings and covered with your favorite fabric or weave. Our rustic cedar benches weather to a soft gray color when left outside yet are resistant to decay and bug infestation. Many of our rustic benches can be customized (as stated on the site) to offer different sizes and configurations.

Search through the wooden blanket box at the foot of your bed when nostalgia hits and discover hidden treasures, warm snuggly blankets, or vintage quilts. Not only terrific for storage but many boxes can double as coffee tables, television stands, or smaller boxes as side tables. Whether rustic reclaimed wood, custom designed blue stained pine, hand waxed alder with dovetailed corners, or cedar patio boxes, we offer it on RusticFurniture.com.

Customize your interior by purchasing multiple bookcases and turning a room into a cozy library or book nook. If reading isn't your fancy use these rustic and beautifully grained bookcases to display some of your treasured collections, special pieces of art, DVD's or add a lamp and light up a corner. Old Hickory offers their classic cases in two different sizes. Place one of the low profile Eastern Rustic cases behind your couch for use as a sofa table. Put a television on the wall between two tall bookcases and have the illusion of an entertainment center. Anyone with children knows that bookcases are a terrific place to store those toys and keep them arranged off the floor.

RusticFurniture.com offers a great variety of rustic furniture from all over North America, and hand selected quality imports too. We have the knowledge and expertise to help you decorate your home or special project. With more than 20 years experience, we have furnished homes and commercial projects all over the globe!
Our Back to Nature line has faux deer antler drawer pulls.

Enhance your dining pleasure with a wide variety of rustic buffet styles ranging from the reclaimed rugged Black Mountain, sophisticated teak Hampton, or multi-colored vintage collection. Various custom styles of hand peeled log and hand distressed alder buffets are fashioned in our Montana showroom. We offer stand alone buffets or entire dining ensembles. Your rustic buffet could be utilized as a TV stand, display area or for extra storage in a great room.

RusticFurniture.com offers some of the sturdiest, classic wood and log bunk beds found online. All of our rustic bunks are constructed entirely in the United States. Rustic aspen, hickory, or pine hand peeled logs are featured in the bunk beds. Using a rustic bunk bed increases the sleeping space in a child's room, hunting retreat or fishing lodge. Bunks are offered in numerous configurations: twin over twin or full, extra long twin over queen, even queen over queen bunk beds. Add another sleeping spot by adding a trundle under any of the rustic bunk beds available.

Solid pine, hammered iron, oversized moldings, and custom cast pulls combine in the Casa Grande Collection to create a very rustic collection of furniture. Wire brushing and deep staining give this furniture a wonderfully rich and textured look that adds to its appeal.

Product.Caption: Dramatically striking hand-hammered and fired copper panels are the eye-catching attraction on the Rustic Copper Canyon Collection. The wood is 100% solid pine and it is enhanced with veneers, hand-forged iron accents and beautiful large rivets.

Solid pine with walnut veneers, the Rustic Cordoba Collection offers a wonderfully rustic appearance with strong, quality craftsmanship. The corners are strengthened with hand-forged iron accents that give a 'hinged' appearance and large iron rivets add to this illusion. The wood is wire brushed, giving it a strong aged look and each piece is completed with a six-step lacquer finish.

In certain homes the rustic coffee table becomes the focal point of the room as it can be used for eating, games, or a great spot to put your feet up. RusticFurniture.com is your perfect resource for this distinctive item. Table tops may be reclaimed rustic planks, quarter sawn oak, pine, hickory, or other native woods. We also offer rustic coffee tables of beautifully grained acacia and sheesham, hardwoods similar to rosewood.

Many of our rustic furniture vendors have several lines of very different collections of rustic furniture. Each image shows a representative piece of furniture from the collection, click on the image to see more pieces in the rustic furniture collections.

Hand forged iron or heavy wood with hand turned legs are the bases for fabulous copper tops in this Rustic Copper Ridge Collection. Each piece is notably unique, yet they blend together for a wonderfully rustic collection of furniture.

Rather than burning or disposing of the wood from demolished old barns, churches, and other structures, Sawtooth Workshop craftsmen find and reclaim these old pieces of wood for rebirth in new uses. The ultimate in recycling, such use of old pieces of wood is not only frugal and eco-friendly, but provides beautiful pieces to be treasured for years to come. The furniture made from this wood is handcrafted and uniquely designed for use as durable rustic furniture. Its finish adds to its beauty and the results are distinctive furniture that will incite interest and compliments and add a touch of history to the furnishings of your home.

Purchase a rustic bookcase to store your CD's or DVD's and place it next to a console where you can store the rest of your entertainment devices.

These items are handcrafted with attention to detail. Imperfections in the wood have been carefully enhanced and filled to bring out the natural character of the piece. The Corvallis collection with clean straight lines made entirely for your dining pleasure is crafted of sheesham, a beautiful cathedral grained plantation grown hardwood available overseas. Call for availability as the distinctive grain is a winner making this collection in high demand.

Remove the ornamentation of drawer hardware and notice the hand distressed craftsmanship of Eastern Rustics Dakota Collection. This beautiful Acacia hardwood, indigenous to India, is dense, heavy and very durable. The collection lends itself to any cabin or rustic bedroom but is also equally suitable for a transitional or more traditional home. Pieces are available for the bedroom, sitting room and dining room. This collection is finished with a warm Dark Cedar finish.

If you have ranching or farming in your family history the rustic Kendari Collection could be just the ticket. The entire collection is historic reclaimed timbers with traditional ornate accents. Each piece's origin has a story of its own. Because of this no two items are exactly the same except for their design. Own a true feeling of timelessness when you purchase a console, end table, coffee table or plasma TV stand in the Kendari Collection. A special lead free lacquer has been applied over the distressed paint on every item in the collection.

Sequoia is one of the collections fashioned of Sheesham, a darker toned dense hardwood. The natural knots, indentations and checks are enhanced and finished to give these furnishings more appeal. Sequoia employs straighter geometrics in their wonderfully solid pieces. This rustic furniture collection offers a variety of sizes for your dining pleasure with both a trestle and traditional four leg dining table. The convenient bench option offers a little more seating space for the youngsters or for a quick informal get together. There is also a coffee and console table in the Sequoia collection.

The Sierra collection, hand crafted from Sheesham, a lovely marbled dense hardwood, has a distinctive look. The dining table is a winner with marbled grain and dark diamond shaped inlay. Table and chair legs feature attractive cabriole design. Sierra features two sizes of table, dining chairs, bar stools and benches plus a personal sized desk.

Fabrics that are most commonly used in Old Hickory Furniture are typically rustic Grade 10 fabrics, because of the wide selection and they are also the most durable. As you go to the 20, 30, 40, 50 and 60 grades the fabrics typically become more complex in composition, texture, and color, but also less durable.
The Clean Peel finish is when all of the bark and cambium are removed using a drawknife, and the furniture is then finished with two coats of water based satin finish.
Our rustic bark finish, is where the firm bark is sanded and left on, then sprayed with two coats of water based satin finish.

This finish means each lodgepole log is hand peeled with a drawknife to leave a small portion of the bark or skip remaining. The our log furniture is finished with two coats of water based satin spray.

Each pine log is peeled partially or entirely with a hand held draw knife in the same manner as logs were peeled a hundred years ago. The striking beauty of the solid, natural guamuchil wood--a durable strong wood native to Mexico and South America--absolutely is the draw on this fabulous collection. Each piece of wood is chosen for its flaws, knots, cracks, and varied shades and colors. If natural wood is the look you are going for, this collection is highly recommended!

Individually handcrafted and one-of-a-kindthose are the key words for the furniture produced in our Rustic Creek Collection. Product.Caption: Rich, darkly stained mango wood, with molded edges on the drawers, hand-turned wooden pulls, and stunning turned, hand painted solid iron legs makes this a practical and gorgeous collection.

Selected solid pine, custom cast hardware, and elegant molded edges give this quality furniture a rustic look all its own. As with all the Artisans furniture, the drawers are constructed with dovetail fronts, mortise and tenon joints and full extension glides on all drawers. You will love the signature simplicity of this collection.
The Back to Nature line comes in either alder (left) or pine (right). You also have the option of staining your furniture in a Golden Pecan or other stain colors.

Montana Renaissance is available in two finishes, Buckskin (bottom) and Aged Mahogany (top). Our alder furniture is distressed and then a hand rubbed wax finish is applied, to make an exceptional looking piece of furniture.
Old Hickory Furniture comes in a variety of leathers, in many colors and textures, we feature a wide selection of rustic and contemporary leathers.

Start with Old Hickory Furniture, one of the country's premier hickory dealers with five different upholstered lines for the living and Great Room. Next add one of our many lines of rustic lamp and coffee tables, sofa tables and consoles, or one of our new plasma television stands. To complete the picture, relax and put your feet up on a comfortable ottoman after a hard day at work.

Almost industrial looking, the functional metal wheels on this collection add so much rustic richness that you might forget about the quality handcraftsmanship, featuring dovetail joinery, ball-bearing glides, and mortise and tenon construction. A weathered-looking, soft brown finish and straight, clean lines add elegance for just that perfect combination.

RusticFurniture.com has handpicked log furniture from premier manufacturers around the country to provide our loyal customers with an extensive variety of choice furnishings that are Made in North America. We offer Aspen, Hickory, Pine and Cedar with many types of bark, peel and finish options. Our rustic log furniture comes from industry leaders around the USA and Canada, including many family businesses and small companies upon which our economy depends. We provide selections for every room of your house from the most durable, elegant rustic log furniture online or in brick and mortar showrooms. Check out our different styles of rustic furnishings and our numerous rustic furniture crafters.

Specializing in rustic log furniture beds and other rustic furnishings, Aspen Ridge Log Furniture offers a line of "one of a kind" designs to capture that special look you desire. Each distinctive item is crafted around the natural flow and beauty of the wood and becomes a functional piece of art unique to your personal space. Aspen Ridge Log Furniture's rugged yet graceful designs bring the outdoors into your home or cabin. Available in a velvety smooth hand rubbed gnarly Aspen or in attractive pine, both furnishings are Made entirely in the USA.

Some people want the best. That even holds true for rustic log furniture design. And for this reason, LodgeCraft Founder, Tom Kincheloe designed the Back to Nature collection over 20 years ago. Long a connoisseur of fine furniture, Tom reasoned that others like himself wanted a product of the highest style and craftsmanship. A rustic furnishing that would stand out from the norm yet be adaptable to variety of lifestyles. That is the goal of LodgeCraft's Back to Nature line. A celebration of nature and fine furniture craftsmanship. In this product, rustic detail is evident from every angle to the discriminating owner. Yes, it is more expensive and takes longer to build, which you will undoubtedly see in the quality.

Since 1973, Frontier Log Furniture by LodgeCraft has been producing furniture from dead standing lodgepole pine. In fact, we think Frontier is the oldest lodgepole pine log furniture manufacturer still in existence. Although many have come and gone, Frontier continues to produce innovative designs of top quality. From the traditional skip peeled Frontier style to the upscale Mission Mountain collection in rustic bark, you will find uncompromising quality and attention to detail delivered by our craftspeople. The rustic bark feature or option we offer on many products, continues to grow in popularity. The Pine Collection features the rustic bark log finish as the standard. Since these furnishings are made in our own Montana workshop, customizing is always welcome. After all, pleasing our customers is why we are still successful after all these years.

Lakeland Mills Cedar furnishings are naturally resistant to decay and insect damage, making them a perfect choice for outdoor lawn furniture and garden accents. Our cedar and pine logs offer green, renewable and environmentally sustainable creations that are by products of the home and plywood industry. Enjoy the subtle grain, beauty, and solid comfort feeling of Lakeland Mills outdoor furniture. Their quality craftsmanship assures years of use and enjoyment. Made in the USA

This is one of the newer lines of rustic furniture that RusticFurniture.com is proud to offer to our customers. This rustic solid line offers rugged yet elegant pieces with specific characters in each creation. All of this aspen log furniture can be custom created to suit your needs. Each of the furniture items seen in the images can be ordered even if they are not listed on our site. Please call with additional inquiries, for more pictures or for commercial projects.

Old Hickory Furniture Company, one of the few remaining original producers of rustic Hickory Furniture, has been around for over 100 years. Since its founder incorporated in 1898 the handcrafting process has remained very much the same. Attention to detail, the careful matching of parts, the difficult assembly with mortise and tenon and the meticulous hand-weaving process, make Old Hickory's products, unique, comfortable, and able to last for generations. Old Hickory has hundreds of rustic furniture pieces in their line yet will also customize to specification. With numerous fabric styles including quality leathers and a wide variety of wood and bark options you can truly create an individual piece for your home. Check out what we have or individualize to your heart's content. RusticFurniture.com offers Free Shipping on Old Hickory Furniture in the lower 48 states. Made in the USA

Whether being used for family picnics, casual gatherings, or tough commercial areas this outdoor cedar furniture will provide many years of pleasure. Cedar is naturally resistant to weather and insect damage. The solid lightweight construction ensures carefree comfort and adds rustic charm, durability and comfort to dining areas and outdoor settings. There is no better way to relax outdoors than in a rustic natural cedar rocker, chair or lounger that has been allowed to age naturally to a beautiful gray patina over the years. Optional cushions can be ordered to add to the comfort of the seating and enhance your decor. Made in the USA.

Our mattresses are made in the Pacific NW, with the finest components. Our supplier is a mid-sized manufacturer of a wide variety of innerspring and foam mattresses. Mattress products range from economical mattress sets to the most luxurious high tech foam and innerspring mattress sets available. The 300 Box Top is our standard mattress. We do have many mattress options available, including a Bamboo Mattress. Please inquire for more mattress options!

A large rustic mirror can be the focal point of a great room or an accent in a bedroom or bath. Our rustic reclaimed Railway Mirrors will make a statement in your cabin or lodge decor. Hang one of the beautiful birch bark Old Hickory Mirrors above your mantel or place it above a sideboard to create an illusion of spaciousness. Rustic mirrors can bring light into any area and offer you a quick peak on your way out the door.

The Mission Mountain Collection, was designed to combine the classic mission style with a rustic bark finish. This Mission Mountain Style has a new truly unequaled spin on traditional log furniture. Handcrafted from Lodgepole Pine Logs the rustic furniture is constructed with the rustic bark left on the logs by a careful hand sanding, resulting in beautiful furnishings with a dark rich yet rustic natural look. Refined pine accents are then added to complete the classic mission Arts and Crafts style.

Each piece of furniture in the Rustic Monte Carlo Collection is constructed of a combination of solid 'recovered' or reclaimed wood and select new wood. Hand distressed and richly stained with a chocolate finish, it makes for gorgeous pieces of very rustic furniture.

Montana Lodge is a Made in America line of rustic furniture offering two distinctive lines. The reclaimed collection and their aspen collection, are both exceptionally well crafted. To see more on either rustic collection, please select the appropriate image link.

Choose from our large selection of rustic and transitional nightstands and end tables including Old Hickory, Shadow Mountain, Eastern Rustic, Montana Lodge, Aspen Ridge, or our own Frontier Log furniture and Montana Renaissance. While these multipurpose rustic furnishings are usually found by the bedside they can stand alone in a variety of locations in your home or cabin. Hickory saplings, reclaimed wood planks, and character woods are incorporated into these distinctive pieces of rustic furniture.

We offer a number of made in the USA desks for the ranging from the smaller LodgeCraft Jim Creek Writing Desk with natural edges, the Frontier Pine Desk or the Old Faithful by Old Hickory to the large Executive Solo Joe with or without a return. For a piece of history check out the Replica Spoke Desk which takes you a step back in time. Add a matching credenza and rustic chair to finish your decorating project.

Old Hickory has many options for most chair and bench backs, including cane, weave and the option of twig or spoke back. Please inquire if an option you desire is not listed for a specific Old Hickory Furniture item.

Old Hickory offers two standard bark options for the hickory saplings on our furniture. Regular Bark is the more natural look, with most of the bark remaining on the sapling. The Regular Bark is lightly sanded removing any loose or sharp areas on the bark leaving a natural looking texture. The Tahoe Bark texture is heavily sanded which exposes some of the inner core and cambium areas of the hickory sapling. The Tahoe Bark texture is a smoother finish and has more variation in colors and texture. Any of our stains can be applied to either bark texture.

Old Hickory uses reclaimed planks of wood from dilapidated old barns torn down across the Midwest, for the premium Aged Barnwood finish. The rustic barnwood still has much of the character that was etched into it from the years of exposure to the elements. It is common to see nail holes, worm holes, mineral streaks, and beautiful patina throughout the pieces. Aged Barnwood is surfaced and sanded smooth. Any stain can be applied, but the lighter the finish the more character will show through. Aged Barnwood is covered with a high quality protective finish to ensure many years of use. Bark edge trim is standard on all aged barnwood furniture.

Wide open spaces in Montana and rustic log retreats are just the place to put your Big Ranch furniture. The modern day rancher has room in his spacious abode to accommodate an entire suite of this "Classic since 1999". Old Hickory decided to reintroduce this collection when customers continued to ask for the line. The large bed is best enhanced by the traditional bark and finish offered. You aren't on a ranch in Montana? That's okay as this collection looks majestic in many decorating themes.

The Buckaroo collection is designed and sized to fit your youngster in Classic Old Hickory style. Old Hickory has been making children's furniture for the past 100 years and are still going strong, even adding to their collection. The weaving and crafting process is the same as that used in adult furnishings. Purchase the two hoop rocker, activity table, wagon wheel rocker or side chair. You can choose the same fabrics you decorate your "big sized" chairs with.

Many Old Hickory Furniture items have the option of cane or weave, which vary in look and composition. Open Cane weave, uses the strongest 3/8" rattan cane available. Wood Splint weave uses 5/8" wide strips of inner core rattan that are woven into a herringbone pattern for superior durability and comfort. Vintage Weave uses 1/2" wide pine-pulp material, that has been used since the 1930's, to give authentic rustic look and comfort. Herringbone Cane is tightly woven 5/16" rattan cane woven in a herringbone pattern. Antique Cane has the same look composition as the Herringbone Cane, except with an antique finish applied.

In the early 1800's, as the pioneers crossed the Appalachian Mountains, among the many discoveries they made was the hickory sapling. This small diameter tree grew throughout the Midwest in groups of twenty to thirty, surrounded by much larger trees. As these saplings struggled towards the sunlight above, they grew straight and tall - yet the diameter did not exceed two to three inches - even after twenty to thirty years of growth. If you're a pioneer without furniture, you soon realize that this amazing hardwood sapling makes ideal chair and table frames. You could soak it in boiling water and bend it to make hoops. You could weave it's inner bark to make seats and backs, and you could see new trees sprout from the same stump - over and over again. And so it became the material of choice for our ancestor's homes. In southern Indiana, a newly transplanted North Carolinian, Billy Richardson, began to make hickory chairs and sell them on Saturdays on the town square in Martinsville. Legend has it that he and his father had made the original Andrew Jackson hoop chairs for the President's home, The Hermitage. Others in the Martinsville area studied Richardson's products and banded together in 1892 in an abandoned church, producing hickory sapling furniture as a full-time business. They chose "Old Hickory" as the company name, the same nick-name as the late President Jackson. When the company incorporated in 1898, a full line of products was available. Shipping across the country to homes and resorts - the company also began furnishing nearly all of the new national park lodges, including the Old Faithful Inn at Yellowstone National Park. The dining chairs in the main hall are the very same chairs shipped and installed in 1906. Today's Old Hickory combines designs from the company's history along with more contemporary applications for home. Yet the process of hand-crafting each piece remains very much the same. Attention to detail, the careful matching of parts, the difficult assembly with mortise and tenon, and the meticulous hand weaving process, make Old Hickory Furniture's products unique, comfortable, and very durable. After one hundred years, old fashioned care continues at Old Hickory Furniture Company, the home of America's genuine, original furniture.

When Robert Reamer was commissioned to design the Old Faithful Lodge in Yellowstone National Park his immediate thought of decor was to ask the Old Hickory Furniture Company to design furnishings for the lodge's Great Room and other showcase rooms The same chairs that were used in the early 1900's still grace the Great room area.

Talk about durability and a lasting impression. The rail at the top of the chair back makes these sturdy hickory furnishings easier to move in and out when holding the seat for your guests. The backs and seats are offered in a variety of weaves, cloths, and leathers, even woven with rawhide or laced leather. With all the options the sky is the limit for your decorating needs.

Old Hickory offers many outdoor fabrics for our rustic hickory furniture. These are more wear resistant and UV resistant, however, it is always best to keep your furniture covered and protected when not in use.
Old Hickory offers quite a few options for your hickory outdoor furniture. Each has different characteristics that allow each piece of rustic furniture its own identity.

Pioneer finish refers to heavily distressed solid oak or solid pine. We offer this premium finish on any of our casegoods or tables. A 9-step finishing process on the solid wood helps to create the worn and weathered look that enhances the value of the furniture. Pioneer Oak and Pioneer Pine can be combined with any of our Bark Textures as well as any of our finish colors. Pioneer finishes do not have bark edge trim.
Old Hickory outdoor furniture has a variety of weave and spoke options for their hickory furniture. See wooden back options here.

Old Hickory uses the highest quality oak and pine veneers available. They are lightly distressed and stained with Puritan, Rustic or Centennial finishes. The veneers are then covered with a high quality finish to protect the surfaces for a long lasting use. Bark edge trim is standard with all veneer products.

One of our favorite collections is Old Hickorys Woodland which uses natural elements at their best. This classic manfacturer takes hickory saplings and wraps them in rustic rawhide strips to incorporate a woven trestle or shelf for your dining table or sideboard. Pull your chairs away from the table and notice this extra display of beauty. In addition the Woodland collection integrates pieces of attractive birch bark to accent the wood chosen for your furnishing. Bring the rustic forest decor into your home with the Woodland Collection. Items offered range from the upholstered line of sofas and chairs to the classic Woodland table designs.

We also carry the complete line of rustic hickory outdoor furniture from Old Hickory, one of the most trusted names in rustic furntiure for over 100 years.

Most people equate Old Hickory furniture with living and dining furnishings but the history of this rustic furniture began in the great outdoors. No matter how much we enjoy our daily work environment it is refreshing to 'take our shoes off' and take a respite in a comfortable chair outside. The rusticity and relaxation offered by Old Hickory outdoor furniture makes this an inviting possibility. You can still purchase many of the same items that grace the porches of historic lodges across the United States. They now apply a dura coat finish which makes it longer lasting and offer a variety of weaves of outdoor friendly materials which all adds up to comfort and sturdiness.

The Pine Collection, manufactured by Frontier Log Furniture in Northwestern Montana, is a step separated from traditional rustic log furnishings. While integrating traditional mortise and tenon log joinery the cambium layer is retained, giving the wood more depth and a rich warm glow that enhances a room's decor. By using non-mechanized harvesting methods on standing dead, beetle-killed Lodgepole Pine, Frontier is proud to offer timeless log furniture products from naturally replenished resources. Full extension ball bearing glides are used on all drawer boxes, environmentally friendly water based satin clear finish and unmatched log furniture styling add to the green. Nothing is better than avoiding cutting live trees to manufacture our log furniture.

A rich finish in cafe-au-lait enhances the European look of this lovely collection. Darker frames around some of the drawers or doors provide a soft contrast and a wonderful old-world flavor. Dovetail joinery and mortise and tenon construction assure quality and years of wear. The hand-forged iron pulls are just the final touches on a beautiful collection.

Our transitional distressed lines of rustic furniture, are truly a great fit in many homes and other rustic settings. With a combination of imported lines and the Montana Made, Renaissance line, we have a style sure to work in your rustic setting. Each image is just a representative image and there are many more pieces and styles in each line.

Remember the way our early American pioneers built their houses using the available timber resources to fashion crude log homes by overlapping the corners and chinking the resulting gaps? As "technology" advanced, these crude dwelling started to morph into a more sophisticated log corner joinery called dovetailing. In dovetailing, the angles of the opposing pieces essential lock together as they are assembled. This is not easily done but the advantages of strength and style are worth the extra time taken. Still considered the pinnacle of present day log home construction, dovetailing is the inspiration for LodgeCraft's own Montana Renaissance collection. Developed by LodgeCraft founder Tom Kincheloe over several years, Montana Renaissance has just the right balance of detailing and style to satisfy the rustic furniture aficionado. Made from alder, a highly renewable west coast hardwood, the finished product features a hand waxed finish that accents the intrinsic rustic features of the lumber and the dovetail joinery and other woodworking detail attributes. Standard line hardware is of antique pewter finish in keeping with the designs inspiration. We do not offer this product to any other retailer, brick and mortar or online. It can only be purchased from the LodgeCraft family of businesses.

Shadow Mountain furniture is a unique collection of distressed imported furniture that is a perfect fit in any rustic setting. Made with the finest components, our Shadow Mountain furniture will provide a lifetime of beauty and durability. Although Shadow Mountain has been discontinued, we have discovered a line that provides similar furniture at similar prices.
